definitions.definition: Possessing the sex organs of both sexes.
Pertaining to a feature or characteristic that is not definitively of either sex .
examples: Nicknames like Pat , Sam , and Chris are androgynous , used by both men and women.

definitions.definition: Able to connect to another connector or port of the same type, rather than being restricted to connecting to solely male or solely female connectors or ports.
examples: APAS is an androgynous docking system, so – in principle, at least – any APAS-equipped vehicle should be able to hook up with any other, without having to worry about matching male with female ports.
labels: of a connector or docking port

main_definition: Possessing the sex organs of both sexes. [from the earlier 17th c.]
